The Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) met weekly with large social media platforms to collaborate on moderating content, according to a deposition this week from FBI Supervisory Special Agent Elvis Chan.

Chan, who was one of the two FBI agents who contacted Facebook ahead of its censoring of the Hunter Biden laptop warning of potential Russian disinformation operations, said that the FBI‚Äôs Foreign Influence Task Force (FITF) and Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency (CISA) officials met weekly with social media companies to remove specific accounts ahead of the 2020 presidential election, according to his deposition cited by Missouri Attorney General Eric Schmitt. _source.content: @SkydogForever  I wore out my cassette(s) of the Allman Brothers concert at Fillmore East. Since then I purchased and still own the double disc CD and have an ABB playlist on my subscription music service. I've been a fan for decades. Although there are many guitarists I admire the three that I came to really tune into early on were Duane Allman, Eric Clapton and George Harrison. Duane spoke through his slide work like no one else. His tone on Live at Fillmore East was phenomenal. Clapton woke the world up with the John Mayall Beano album and set the world on fire with his stint in the virtuoso supergroup Cream. George Harrison made the landmark album All Things Must Pass which is still something to marvel at. His grace and style is unmatched.
